<dl id="un1013bp"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="un1" href="#un1013">UN1: </a>  <a href="../../FF/unbs/un1all.htm#un1013bp"> (NLI.3) 13(bp)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <u>serpent fires</u> from spine to crown, <small>Not cancelled</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="un1013bp"><li>Ulysses </li><li><a href="../../ulex/n/lexn.htm#un1013bp">2021</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/n/n86.htm#un1013bp">2017</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/n/n86.htm#un1013bp">1986 (12.341f)</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/n/l22n.htm#un1013bp">1922</a> </li><li><ms href="#un1013bp">MS V.A.8-5v</ms> </li><li>JJA 13:094 </li><li><a name="n1B1d" href="../udra/u12da.htm#n1B1d">Usage</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/n/n1B1d.htm#un1013bp">Draft: 12B.1</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">&hellip; to bring the first centre into activity is precisely to awaken the <mark>serpent-fire</mark>. When once that is aroused, it is by its tremendous force that the other centres are vivified. &hellip; the navel, &hellip; the man begins in the physical body to be conscious of all kinds of astral influences &hellip; the spleen, &hellip; the man is enabled to remember his vague astral journeys, &hellip; half-remembrances of a blissful sensation of flying through the air. &hellip; the heart, makes the man instinctively aware of the joys and sorrows of others, and sometimes even causes him to reproduce in himself by sympathy their physical aches and pains. &hellip; the throat, enables him to hear voices, &hellip; between the eye-brows,&hellip; the man begins to see things, to have various sorts of waking visions, &hellip; full arousing of this brings about clairvoyance. <small> <a name="THmay1910" href="/udra/udex.htm#THmay1910"><cite title="source">The Theosophist</cite></a> (May 1910), C.W. Leadbeater, &ldquo;FORCE-CENTRES AND THE SERPENT-FIRE&rdquo; p. 1082-83</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c07260g" href="../../../F/FF/fnbs/c07all.htm#c07260g">VI.C.07:260(g)</a> </dd> </dd></dl>
